text: Allocasuarina monilifera, commonly known as necklace sheoak, is a shrub of the genus Allocasuarina native to Tasmania and Victoria. The medium shrub typically grows to a height of less than . It grows in a variety of regions including coastal and sub-alpine. ==References== ==External links== * Occurrence data for Allocasuarina monilifera from The Australasian Virtual Herbarium monilifera Category:Flora of Tasmania Category:Flora of Victoria (Australia) Category:Fagales of Australia
